        'You are the Chief Risk Officer at Amanah Tijarah Bank Berhad. Upload ISL_01_Financing_Portfolio.xlsx to Analyst and use the Murabahah Book, Tawarruq Tracker, and Ijarah Portfolio tabs to quantify which contracts, sectors, and customer groups are driving the increase in Stage 2 financing. Estimate how much of total stress comes from the top 10 exposures, show the gross impaired financing trend, and highlight where documentation exceptions overlap with credit deterioration. Flag exposures requiring immediate remediation as Red, exposures needing tighter watchlist treatment as Amber, and exposures showing stabilisation as Green. Present as a RAG table.',
        'You are the Group Treasurer at Amanah Tijarah Bank Berhad. Upload ISL_01_Financing_Portfolio.xlsx to Analyst and use the GIA Performance and Wakalah Summary tabs to assess how further runoff, repricing pressure, or profit-equalisation support would affect liquidity, earnings, and sukuk readiness over the next 2 quarters. Show where displaced commercial risk is most acute, and identify whether management has enough buffer before the MYR 2.4B Sukuk Wakalah programme launches. Flag scenarios with immediate liquidity or earnings pressure as Red, manageable pressure as Amber, and resilient scenarios as Green. Present as a RAG table.',
